snippet.textDisplay: Glad you're trying to stay positive in this for everyone... My Dad is enduring an incurable form of prostate cancer & it's hard to stay positive over things like that when you know there's nothing you can do to fix it. One of his favorite phrases to say "When you wake up in the morning just thank God for 1 more day", & though I get concerned about the pain he goes through, at least his wife, my Mom, is there to help & he still tries to get things done through it all & still tries to enjoy all his hobbies.

snippet.textDisplay: Amazing my father has been battling kidney cancer for 2 years that first year was the hardest he was literally on his death bead everyone was saying their goodbyes! Watching him go thru the therapy every week and get sick is sad but it's only for his best interest! I'm so grateful for these options in cancers treatments! If he had gotten cancer just a few years ago he wouldn't be here I'm so grateful for the break thru in the immunotherapy my father is still here fighting 👊💥 I'm so happy to see you still here and fighting 👊💥ur fight as well Jeporady wouldn't be the same without you!!
